# KeryxPro Development Walkthrough

We have successfully established the technical foundation (Phase 1), implemented the primarily interactive Song UI (Phase 2), and completely wired up the cross-pane Song Preview Logic (Phase 3) for KeryxPro!

## Phase 1 & 2 Recap
- Scaffolding of the Clean Architecture pattern using Riverpod + Isar 3.x database.
- Implemented `DashboardApp` for primary views and `ProjectorApp` for secondary Go-Live screens.
- Connected the `SongLibraryTab` to perform real-time SQL full-text searching using an `AsyncNotifierProvider`.

## Phase 3 Accomplishments: The Preview Pane

We successfully connected the disparate panes of your UI using Riverpod's reactive graph, demonstrating how easily we can route projection data!

### Global Cross-Pane States
Created `selectedSongProvider`, a simple `StateProvider` living above the UI tree. The `SongLibraryTab` (Left Pane) was updated so that `onTap`, it simply registers the targeted `Song` with this provider. 

### Lyric Parsing Engine (`PreviewPane`)
Replaced the Right Pane placeholder with the new `PreviewPane`. When a user clicks a song:
1. The Preview Pane instantly rebuilds via Riverpod's listening mechanisms.
2. It fetches the text-blob `lyrics` string from Isar.
3. It utilizes a `RegExp(r'\n\s*\n')` split execution to slice the lyrics precisely on double-newlines.
4. Each stanza is dynamically wrapped in a modern, styled `Card` displaying its Slide Number and text boundaries.

### Validation Details
The system now functions as a unified previewer. If no song is selected, the preview pane gracefully falls back to a helper instruction screen. Clicking an item immediately slices that content up to mimic individual projection bounds.

